<h2 id="Syntax" name="Syntax">Syntax</h2>
<pre class="twopartsyntaxbox"><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax" title="CSS/Value_definition_syntax">Formal syntax</a>: <code>show <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Single_bar" title="Single bar: the two entities are optional, but exactly one must be present.">|</a> hide</code>
</pre>
<pre>empty-cells: show
empty-cells: hide

empty-cells: inherit</pre>
<h3 id="Values" name="Values">Values</h3>
<dl><dt>
  <code>show</code></dt>
 <dd>
  Is a keyword indicating that borders and backgrounds should be drawn like in normal cells.</dd>
 <dt>
  <code>hide</code></dt>
 <dd>
  Is a keyword indicating that no borders or backgrounds should be drawn.</dd>
</dl>